# TDD/BDD Development Standard [MANDATORY]

## Core Principles

1. **Test-First Development [REQUIRED]**: All code must be developed following Test-Driven Development (TDD) principles:
   - Tests MUST be written BEFORE implementation code
   - Implementation code should only be written to make failing tests pass
   - All tests must pass before code is considered complete

2. **Behavior-Driven Development [REQUIRED]**: All user stories must include Behat/Gherkin scenarios:
   - Each acceptance criterion must have at least one corresponding Behat scenario
   - Scenarios must be written in GIVEN/WHEN/THEN format
   - Scenarios must be executable and integrated with the testing framework

3. **Code Coverage Requirements [MANDATORY]**:
   - All code must achieve minimum 80% test coverage
   - All public methods must have unit tests
   - All business logic must have integration tests
   - All user-facing functionality must have acceptance tests

## User Story Standard Format

All user stories MUST include the following acceptance criterion:

```
Development follows strict TDD/BDD approach with unit tests written before implementation code and minimum 80% code coverage
```

This criterion is a prerequisite for all other acceptance criteria - no other acceptance criteria can be considered complete until this criterion is satisfied.

## Implementation Requirements

### 1. Unit Testing

- All classes must have corresponding unit test classes
- Unit tests must be written before implementation code
- Unit tests must verify:
  - Expected behavior
  - Edge cases
  - Error conditions
  - Type safety

### 2. Integration Testing

- All integrations between components must be tested
- Database interactions must be tested
- External API interactions must be mocked and tested
- File system operations must be tested

### 3. Acceptance Testing

- All user-facing functionality must have Behat scenarios
- Scenarios must cover all acceptance criteria
- Scenarios must be executable in the CI/CD pipeline
- Visual elements must be tested with screenshot comparisons

## Definition of Done

Code cannot be considered "Done" unless:

1. Tests were written before implementation code
2. All tests are passing
3. Code coverage meets the minimum 80% threshold
4. Behat scenarios exist for all acceptance criteria
5. All tests are included in the automated test suite

## Tool Usage

- PHPUnit for unit and integration testing
- Behat for acceptance testing
- PHPCodeCoverage for measuring code coverage
- WP_Mock for mocking WordPress functions

## Sprint Process Integration

1. **Planning Phase**:
   - Create Behat features for all user stories
   - Define scenarios for all acceptance criteria

2. **Development Phase**:
   - Write unit tests before implementation code
   - Create integration tests for component interactions
   - Run tests continuously

3. **Review Phase**:
   - Verify test coverage meets requirements
   - Execute all tests to verify functionality
   - Review test quality and completeness

## Enforcement

This standard applies to ALL code development without exception. No code will be accepted that doesn't meet these requirements.

The Software Engineering Team (SET) is responsible for enforcing these standards and ensuring all code follows the TDD/BDD approach. 